parameters: People4
I'm sorry son but I'm really busy right now.
People4
Welcome. I’ve been expecting you.
Actor2
Then you know why I’m here I presume?
People4
Of course. You’re concerned about the recent
disasters. I assure you that everything is
under control.
Actor2
So you’ve thought about how you’re going to
save the nature spirit?
People4
Nature spirit? Oh heavens no!  These floods
have destroyed citizens’ homes, and as Mayor
I need to see to it that they’re
accommodated.
Actor2
So you’re doubling down?
People4
Precisely.
Actor2
For the sake of everyone, you have to
reconsider.
A
People4
You may have convinced PRODUCER and Patty
of your dream, but I know what’s best for
the people.
You should know what’s best for the people
You’re also at risk from all this
You should know what’s best for the people
Actor2
If you know what’s best for the people,
then you should know that doubling down will
only displace more people and cause more
suffering.
People4
We don’t know that until we try. If we keep
developing, we can recover what we’ve lost
and keep developing our technology at a
faster rate.
People4
We can plan our architecture around these
disasters and eventually create technology
that will make the nature spirit irrelevant.
Technology has only hurt the nature spirit
It’s not too late to reverse things
Technology has only hurt the nature spirit
Actor2
The advancement of technology has only
served to hurt the nature spirit in the
past.  It won’t be any different now.
The more we advance, the worse things get.
People4
Even if it’s as you say, we can still
improve the architecture and make it
disaster-proof as we expand.
This isn’t a race we win
It’s not possible to rebuild the entire town
This isn’t a race we win
Actor2
That’s not going to work. The disasters
will become too much to handle, and the
town is going to be wiped out!
This isn’t a race we win.
People4
We don’t know that until we try. Nobody
knows for sure what happens when the nature
spirit dies. For all we know, the nature
spirit dying will stop everything.
People4
Hell, there’s an idea.  Destroy the nature
spirit now and skip the hard part!
It’s not possible to rebuild the entire town
Actor2
It’s not possible to rebuild the entire
town as it’s lost, and even then, the
disasters are going to get worse and worse.
Actor2
There’s no way that everyone makes it out
of that struggle unscathed. You’re
sacrificing more people than you would be
if you just stopped now!
People4
Hmm… You have a point, that would be
difficult. Even so, stopping expansion will
drop the quality of life of everyone
involved.
People4
The economy will stagnate and the people
will be unhappy.
Expanding won’t be sustainable either.
Town's longevity is more important
Expanding won’t be sustainable either.
Actor2
Expanding won’t be sustainable either. As
we progress, we will destroy ecosystems and
make entire species of animals go extinct.
Actor2
Natural resources will run out and the
town’s economy will stagnate anyway..
People4
Very well. I can consult the people on the
matter, but I doubt they’ll agree to this.
You are the one in charge not the people!
The people are scared and need your leadership
You are the one in charge not the people!
Actor2
The people aren’t the ones in charge, you
are. All you have to do is listen to me and
this will all work out.
People4
You don’t understand a thing about me, do
you? I am a servant of the people, first
and foremost.
People4
I will not move forward on a plan that I
didn’t concoct myself without their
approval.
The people are scared and need your leadership
Actor2
The people are scared, Mayor White! Some
have lost their homes, and others have seen
it firsthand!
Actor2
They’ll go with anything you propose as
long as you say it with conviction!
Just listen to me and we’ll all get through
this!
People4
You… you’re right. Perhaps I’ve been
listening to PRODUCER too much. I’ll listen
to what you have to say.
Stop chopping trees after the people have been humbled
Slow down expantion to avoid problems in our lifetime
Slow down expansion and allow the forest to regrow
Stop chopping trees after the people have been humbled
Actor2
We need to stop chopping down the forests
immediately. The people have been humbled
by these disasters, and just want their
futures secured.
Actor2
They’ll be happy with that certainty
returned to them.
People4
This is acceptable, if it means that the
most people possible are safe, I’m willing
to oblige.
B
Slow down expantion to avoid problems in our lifetime
Actor2
We slow down expansion and the destruction
of the forest, but don’t stop it entirely.
The problem won’t become extreme within our
lifetimes.
People4
And pass the problem to future generations?
I really thought you had something better
prepared.
Slow down expansion and allow the forest to regrow
Actor2
Well, when I was talking to PRODUCER, I
proposed to him that we could slow
expansion and regrow the forests.
Actor2
Profits will take a bit of a hit, and
expansion will slow somewhat, but that
should stop these disasters from happening.
People4
That sounds like a win-win. I’m not
surprised PRODUCER agreed to this idea.
We will make a plan immediately.
B
Town's longevity is more important
Actor2
A drop in quality of life for everyone is a
small price to pay to save lives and the
environment. Think about the longevity of
this town!
People4
I’ve thought well and hard about the
longevity of this town, and I’ve determined
that this is the best course of action.
It’s not too late to reverse things
Actor2
It’s unfortunate, but if we leave the
people who lost their homes to this behind
it’s not too late to reverse things.
People4
As a servant of the people I’m afraid I
cannot agree to that.
You’re also at risk from all this
Actor2
You know, you’re also at risk from all this.
If the health of the spirit declines enough,
your livelihood will be at risk, same as us.
People4
I am just a cog in the system.  I will put
it at risk no less than any other citizen.
You’re being overdramatic.
People4
Thank you for everything you did to this
town and nature spirit!
People4
You can tell that the mayor really cares
about all of us and the wellbeing of this
town. His heart is in the right place, but
he’s misguided.
People1
I'm looking for old records about the town
to show my kid how the town used to be when
I grew up.
People4
Ever since my husband brought these books
to our bedroom for convenience it seems
that he can never properly rest anymore.
People4
He works himself too much sometimes if you
ask me.
Actor1
I’m afraid the mayor is not expecting any
visitors right now.
Actor1
The mayor is expecting you.
Actor1
I’m afraid the mayor is not expecting any
visitors right now.
